In this program, the counts function takes a string as input and counts the occurrences of each character in the string. It does this by iterating over each character in the string and adding it to a dictionary. If the character already exists in the dictionary, its count is incremented by 1. If not, the character is added to the dictionary with an initial count of 1.

The program then calls the counts function with the input string "aba" and prints the resulting dictionary. It also demonstrates how the function handles an empty string and returns an empty dictionary in this case.
